#Adopted(Dwarf)-Goldsniffer		KEY:Adopted Goldsniffer ~ Trait					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Goldsniffer ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Dwarf		DESC:Your adoptive dwarven parents honed your keen senses in finding hidden treasures. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Perception checks related to metals, jewels, and gemstones.																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.331
#Adopted(Dwarf)-Tunnel Fighter	KEY:Adopted Tunnel-Fighter ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Tunnel Fighter ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Dwarf		DESC:Having been adopted by dwarves, caves and tunnels are a second home to you. While underground, you receive a +2 trait bonus on initiative checks and a +1 trait bonus on weapon damage rolls for critical hits (this damage is multiplied on a critical hit).																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.331
#Adopted(Elf)-Forlorn		KEY:Adopted Forlorn ~ Trait							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Forlorn ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Elf		DESC:You were been adopted and raised by elves outside of traditional elf society, you know the world can be cruel, dangerous, and unforgiving of the weak.																																										BONUS:CHECKS|Fortitude|1|TYPE=Trait																		SOURCEPAGE:p.331
#Adopted(Elf)-Warrior of Old		KEY:Adopted Warrior of Old ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Warrior of Old ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Elf	DESC:Your adoptive elf parents put you through long hours of combat drills, and though time has made this training a dim memory, you still have a knack for quickly responding to trouble.																																														BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|2|TYPE=Trait																			SOURCEPAGE:p.331
#Adopted(Gnome)-Animal Friend	KEY:Adopted Animal Friend ~ Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Animal Friend ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Gnome		DESC:Having been adopted and raised by gnomes, you have long been a friend to animals, and feel safer when there are animals nearby. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Will saving throws as long as an animal (Tiny or larger, must be at least indifferent toward you) is within 30 feet.																																																						CSKILL:Handle Animal	SOURCEPAGE:p.331
#Adopted(Gnome)-Rapscallion	KEY:ADopted Rapscallion ~ Trait					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Rapscallion ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Gnome		DESC:You were adopted by gnomes and spent your entire life thumbing your nose at the establishment and took pride in your runins with the law. Somehow, despite all the mischievous behavior in your life, you've never been caught.																																							BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|1|TYPE=Trait	BONUS:SKILL|Escape Artist|1|TYPE=Trait											SOURCEPAGE:p.331
#Adopted(Half-Elf)-Elven Reflexes	KEY:Adopted Elven Reflexes ~ Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Elven Reflexes ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Half-Elf			DESC:One of your adoptive half-elf parents was a member of a wild elven tribe, and you've inherited a portion of your elven parent's quick reflexes.																																																				BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|2|TYPE=Trait																		SOURCEPAGE:p.331
#Adopted(Half-Elf)-Failed Apprentice	KEY:Adopted Failed Apprentice ~ Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Failed Apprentice ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Half-Elf			DESC:As a child, your adoptive  half-elf parents sent you to a distant wizard's tower as an apprentice so that you might learn the arcane arts. Unfortunately, you had no arcane talent whatsoever, though you did learn a great deal about the workings of spells and how to resist them.																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.331
#Adopted(Orc)-Brute			KEY:Adopted Brute ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Brute ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Half-Orc			DESC:You were adopted by Orcs to work for a crime lord, either as a lowlevel enforcer or as a guard, and became adept at frightening away people.																																																												BONUS:SKILL|Intimidate|1|TYPE=Trait								CSKILL:Intimidate		SOURCEPAGE:p.332
#Adopted(Orc)-Outcast		KEY:Adopted Outcast ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Outcast ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Half-Orc			DESC:You were adopted by Orcs and driven from town after town because of their heritage, you have become adept at living apart from others.																																																														BONUS:SKILL|Survival|1|TYPE=Trait								CSKILL:Survival		SOURCEPAGE:p.332
#Adopted(Halfling)-Freedom Fighter	KEY:Adopted Freedom Fighter ~ Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Freedom Fighter ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Halfling			DESC:Your adoptive halfling parents allowed escaping slaves to hide in your home, and the stories you've heard from them instilled into you a deep loathing of slavery. You gain a +1 trait bonus on any skill check or attack roll made during the process of escaping capture or in helping a slave escape bondage.																																													CSKILL:Escape Artist	SOURCEPAGE:p.332
#Adopted(Halfling)-Well-Informed	KEY:Adopted Well Informed ~ Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Well Informed ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Halfling			DESC:Having been adopted by halflings, you make it a point to know everyone and to be connected to everything around you. You frequent the best taverns, attend all of the right events, and graciously help anyone who needs it. Because of this, you gain a +1 trait bonus on Diplomacy checks to gather information.			STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (Local)|Diplomacy																		BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Local)|1|TYPE=Trait						CSKILL:LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.332
#Adopted(Human)-Scholar of Ruins	KEY:Adopted Scholar of Ruins ~ Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted Scholar of Ruins ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Human		DESC:From the moment you were adopted by humans, the ruins of ancient civilizations have fascinated you. Because of this, you have special insight into geography as well as expertise in exploring lost places.															STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (Geography)|Knowledge (Dungeoneering)														BONUS:SKILL|LIST|1|TYPE=Trait	CSKILL:LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.332
#Adopted(Human)-World Traveler	KEY:Adopted World Traveler ~ Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Adopted World Traveler ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]		!PRERACE:1,Human		DESC:Your adopted human family has taken the love of travel to an extreme, roaming the world extensively. You've seen dozens of cultures and have learned to appreciate the diversity of what the world has to offer.																STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (Local)|Diplomacy|Sense Motive															BONUS:SKILL|LIST|1|TYPE=Trait									CSKILL:LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.332
